definition: The average monthly search volume for a keyword in Google Search over the past 12 months. Represents the number of times users searched for a specific keyword per month.
notes: Values are rounded. Volume can vary by location and language.

definition: Cost Per Click - the average price advertisers pay per click for a keyword in Google Ads. Indicates commercial intent and keyword value.
notes: Currency is typically USD. Higher CPC often indicates higher commercial value.

definition: A value from 0 to 1 representing the level of competition among advertisers for a keyword in Google Ads. 1 = highest competition.
notes: This is paid search competition, not organic SEO competition.

definition: Estimated Traffic Volume - the estimated organic traffic a page receives from ranking for a keyword, calculated as search_volume Ã— CTR for the rank position.
notes: Higher positions receive higher CTR, thus higher ETV.

definition: The organic search ranking position (1-100) of a URL for a specific keyword in Google Search results.
notes: Position 1 is the top result. Positions beyond 100 are typically not tracked.

definition: The organic search ranking position of a URL for a specific keyword. Same as 'rank'.
notes: Lower position numbers indicate higher visibility.

definition: The absolute ranking position in SERP including all result types (organic, ads, featured snippets, etc).
notes: May differ from organic rank due to SERP features above organic results.

definition: The estimated monthly organic traffic to a domain or page, calculated from keyword rankings, search volumes, and expected CTR.
notes: This is an estimate based on known keyword rankings.

definition: A proprietary ranking score (0-1000) representing the overall authority/strength of a domain based on backlinks and other factors.
notes: Similar to Domain Authority (Moz) or Domain Rating (Ahrefs).

definition: The total number of backlinks (inbound links) pointing to a domain or page from external websites.
notes: Includes both dofollow and nofollow links.

definition: The number of unique domains linking to a target domain or page. A subset of backlinks that counts each domain only once.
notes: More referring domains generally indicates a more natural link profile.

definition: The low range of what advertisers pay for a top-of-page ad placement in Google Ads.
notes: Useful for estimating minimum ad spend for competitive keywords.

definition: The high range of what advertisers pay for a top-of-page ad placement in Google Ads.
notes: Represents premium positions at the top of search results.

definition: A score (0-100) estimating how difficult it would be to rank organically for a keyword based on current top-ranking pages.
notes: Higher scores indicate more competition and established authority needed.

definition: Classification of a domain based on its business model: OEM/Manufacturer, Service Provider, Marketplace, End Customer, Educational/Media, or Irrelevant.
notes: Used for competitive analysis and business relevance scoring.

definition: Classification of a URL/page type: Product/Service, Category, Blog/Article, Resource/Guide, Pricing, Landing Page, About, Support, etc.
notes: Used for prioritizing SEO actions and content strategy.

definition: The user intent classification of a page: Transactional, Commercial Investigation, Informational, Navigational, or Support.
notes: Helps determine SEO priority and content optimization strategy.

definition: A weighted score (0-100) combining ETV, intent, page type, and business relevance to rank pages for SEO priority.
notes: Higher scores indicate higher priority for SEO action.

definition: Categorization of pages into priority tiers for SEO action: Tier 1 (Immediate), Tier 2 (High), Tier 3 (Medium), Tier 4 (Monitor), Tier 5 (Ignore).
notes: Derived from priority_score for actionable segmentation.

definition: Recommended SEO action for a page: High Priority Target, Create Equivalent Page, Optimize Existing Page, Add to Content Cluster, Backlink Prospect, Monitor Only, or Ignore.
notes: Actionable recommendation derived from page analysis.

definition: Boolean indicating whether a SERP result appears as a featured snippet (position 0) at the top of Google search results.
notes: Featured snippets receive significantly higher CTR than regular results.

definition: The total number of keywords for which a domain or page ranks in organic search results.
notes: Indicates the organic search footprint of a domain.

definition: The estimated cost to acquire the same traffic through paid ads in Google Ads, based on keyword CPCs and traffic volume.
notes: Useful for valuing organic traffic in monetary terms.

definition: A numeric code identifying the geographic location for search data. Common codes: 2840 (US), 2356 (India), 2826 (UK).
notes: Search volumes and rankings vary by location.

definition: A two-letter ISO 639-1 code identifying the language for search data (e.g., 'en' for English, 'hi' for Hindi).
notes: Search volumes and rankings vary by language.

definition: The date when the data was captured from the DataForSEO API.
notes: SEO data changes over time; snapshot date indicates data freshness.

definition: The timestamp when the data was fetched and stored in the system.
notes: Indicates when the data was last updated in the local database.

definition: The timestamp of the most recent data pull from the external API.
notes: Same as fetched_at; indicates data freshness.
